            "pspeech": "Adj-ANS",
            "description": " hurtful, i.e. evil (properly, in effect or influence, and thus differing from \u03ba\u03b1\u03ba\u1f79\u03c2(kak\u00f3s), which refers rather to essential character, as well as from \u03c3\u03b1\u03c0\u03c1\u1f79\u03c2(sapr\u00f3s), which indicates degeneracy from original virtue); figuratively, calamitous; also (passively) ill, i.e. diseased; but especially (morally) culpable, i.e. derelict, vicious, facinorous; neuter (singular) mischief, malice, or (plural) guilt; masculine (singular) the devil, or (plural) sinners"
        },
